<user_name>Sam Ledwitz<//user_name>< Review>
Last night, my daughter graduated 8th grade and all she wanted was her favorite food from Phuket Thai.  We've been going there for years and they have the best chicken skewers and soup ever.  I had the shrimp and mushroom diner and it was delicious.  Also, the have fantastic yummy rice that is not just your regular white rice.  It is made with care and tastes amazing.  Love it.  My daughter also got a chocolate raspberry cake (not from Phuket) to go along with the yummy food.  All in all, she had a very enjoyable dinner and a great graduation (even with all the Covid stuff going on in the world).< /Review>

<review>Impress your friends without going broke. Ive eaten at many nice Thai restaurants, even Vegetarian Thai. This was wonderful! Good size portions, but not obnoxious. (I had left over) The Spring rolls were fresh and presented like a carefully wrapped  gift. Not tossed on a bare plate. The chicken coconut soup was perfect. Lemongrass gave that needed tart that you seek in this creamy dish. I was able to order my soup "small" delightful! I almost didn't order it till I saw I had that choice. Thai ice tea was delicate and not too sweet! I watched the Sun go down and view was very relaxing. Wait staff was courteous and attentive. Quick, clean, classic. Nice wine menu as well. Worth a try, I dont think you'll regret it. Lunch specials looked like a value. No dress code but you may feel like its leave the muscle shirt at home. I tipped a deserved 20% Thank you for being so good!<//review>< pics>

<Date>1505786540181<//Date>< rating>
4< /rating>
<review>I actually used Yelp to find this place because I was craving some birria tacos.  This place was an unsuspecting diamond in the rough.  It's a cozy space located in a little strip mall off La Habra blvd.  And if you don't pay attention you might miss it.

First off the service was excellent.  We came in with a party of 7, but there was only one table big enough to fit us with the reserved sign on it. When we inquired about the tables, the response was, "we saved if for you".

Secondly, all the food looked amazing.  The carne asada was juicy and not dry, the chicken was moist, the shrimp was perfectly cooked. Birria tacos were a little bit on the dry side, but very edible and still yummy. All the veggies were fresh. Salsa's were made fresh with red and green variety.  Best part, portions were big and definitely worth the prices.

Tacos were $1.65 each, but they were stuffed with $1.65 worth of meat and veggies.  Super Nacho's were $11.99, but came with chicken, carve asada, big juicy shrimp, guacamole, and fresh air cream all over to fresh cooked tostada chips.  Quesadillas overfilled with cheese and meat.

Once finished our server was nice enough to split the checks 7 ways! If I'm in the area again, this is the place I'll be coming to get my Mexican food fix.<//review><pictures>None< /pictures>< response>
None<//response>

< Text>
I love this place!  I've been to this location several times and always get great, friendly service but this weekend topped the others. I decided to install some synthetic turf in my back yard and do it myself. I've had a couple material deliveries from Southwest (delivered the day and time promised) and on Saturday I was finalizing the top layer of decomposed granite before laying the turf.
Well, I realized I was about two yards short and headed to SW Boulder. My truck can handle 1/2 yard at-a-time, so I was hurrying. They were quick and efficient each time but my last trip was going to have me arrive a couple minutes after closing.
I called to see if they could help and the manager, Christian, said "come on down and I'll help you out".  I was so stoked to have that kind of service in today's world.
With the new world of Amazon instant delivery and so many stores closing, I want to make sure we'll run, customer oriented businesses like Southwest remain open.
This place is the top of my recommendation list.<//Text>

I strongly disagree with MC. I use Southwest pretty often, and I am always impressed. They have very good customer service and an amazing selection. Make sure you go up to their big yard in Rainbow if you want to see all of your choices, though. The PB yard is just a small selection of what they can get for you. I love picking boulders from them because they have about 20 different kinds, way more than anyone else, and they let you climb all over the piles and pick any specific boulder you want. These guys function like a family owned business (which I think they are) and really go the extra mile.< /text>

< review>
Our Pawgo Groomer visited our home, grooming both of my dogs. I noticed when she was loading them in and out of her van, she wasn't using a proper lifting technique - but didn't want to correct the "professional" while she was taking care of my pups. Later that afternoon both of my dogs started to show signs of back injury, like pain when being pet. I hoped it was minor and would resolve itself, but unfortunately a trip to the vet and a round of xrays show that one my dogs, had a slipped disk and paresis from trauma. She will now potentially need MRI scans and surgery if we're unable to resolve it from home. Both of my dogs started showing signs of mishandling after their groom. Back pain, bruises on their rear, a rash from their bath a few days later. I contacted corporate team - after reviewing xrays and talking to the groomer, they offered me a $50 credit - not even a 3rd of the cost of their groom. They didn't offer to cover the medical costs or even refund my groom. so disappointed.<//review>

< review>
I've been at this bar a couple of times for concerts. Even though the view on the stage is exceptional, I give this note because of the way I was treated by the staff (ownership) after being attacked, twice, by the same person, coming to see the concerts as well. Some co-owners treated me as if I was the attacker, literally accusing me of wanting to make trouble, and physically pushing me when I was trying to defend myself because the security wouldn't do it, as the only persons who stopped the attacker were other attendees of the show. The security put no pressure on this person to stop.

As I had been targeted by this person for the second time in the same place, I called a police officer a couple of nights later, purposefully on a day when there was nothing happening there (and practically no one inside, even less outside in the street), for a report against my attacker, and asked the members of the bar staff present if they could give him their testimony after what they've seen. The security played the game, but the ownership behaved ridiculously bad towards me. Pretending they had never seen me, which was false. Pretending they didn't know who my attacker was, which as I found out later was false again. Finding a stratagem to lead me out of the bar when I would speak with the officer, and then leave the security to tell me that I was forbidden to come back in. Because the staff of this bar didn't want to admit that they had not handled well the attack I had been victim of in the first place, and so they didn't accept that I would call the police, even for a simple report, even on an evening where there was nothing happening at the bar, even though the officer was very kind and that there's no way his presence at the entrance for a few minutes could have caused any prejudice to the bar. The bar staff wasn't willing to see that I had called the police because they themselves had showed to be unable (and / or unwilling) to deal correctly with the person attacking me. Maybe because this person is American, and ostensibly wealthy and socially surrounded, while I am not.

Once again, I don't blame any member of the security individually, I blame the ownership that seemed to be only interested in keeping a reputation they visibly don't deserve, and keep getting the money deriving from it. The least of their concerns was the way I felt after their failing to take in charge my attacker, and then again after their unjustified, dishonest and violent attitude, when I only wanted a testimony from them, which was the least they could've done for me at that point.

Edit: for info a few persons left a review right after mine which happen to be my attacker (Jessica Deen) and a few of her friends : Erin Ryan, Montclare, Alison Munin, Shelby McElrath, to mention only them (but seeing the time coincidence, there seems to be several others, since I haven't myself written this review right after the gig, more like a week after, but they have all written their reviews simultaneously and immediately after mine...), which have all known of me online, and have been apparentely following me everywhere on internet lately. Funny to see that these persons barely have written any Google reviews apart from this one. All adding to their sad history of online and real life bullying attempts. Which seems to take most of their time. Good luck guys!< /review>

< text>
I visited this location based on a referral as I was told that it catered to the needs of individuals who had foot problems and needed to be fitted with special athletic footwear. Please note that this isn't a regular sporting goos store which simply sells sneakers. If you require special sneakers that would fit the contours of your foot or walking style, this is definitely the place to visit. However, please bare in mind that that they cater to those who are flat-footed, those who place excess pressure on their heels or on the balls of your feet or otherwise when walking then this is definitely the place to visit. They do complete scans of your feet and walking styles before you're fitted with your type of shoe by a specialist. Be prepared to spend a minimum of $150.00 depending on your condition. However, you'd be pleased with the results!<//text>
